Q. Find the reverse of a number provided by the user(any number of digit) .
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Solution:

def fun(n):
    s=str(n)
    if s[0]=='-':
        reverse_num="-"+s[:-(len(s)):-1]
    else:
        reverse_num=s[::-1]
    return int(reverse_num)
n=int(input("enter a number"))
fun(n)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Output:

enter a number 1234
4321
